I am trying to simulate the following generated SV module along with it's testbench:

**Design: `counter.sv`**

```systemverilog
//==============================================================================
//
// The code is generated by Intel Compiler for SystemC, version 1.3.31
// see more information at https://github.com/intel/systemc-compiler
//
//==============================================================================

//==============================================================================
//
// Module: Dut ()
//
module Dut // "tb.dut_inst"
(
    input logic clk,
    input logic rstn,
    output logic [3:0] counter,
    output logic even
);

//------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Clocked THREAD: threadProc (dut.h:26:5) 

// Thread-local variables
logic [3:0] counter_next;

// Next-state combinational logic
always_comb begin : threadProc_comb     // dut.h:26:5
    threadProc_func;               //<   Comment this line for iverilog simulation to work
    //counter_next = counter;      //< Uncomment this line for iverilog simulation to work
    //counter_next = counter + 1;  //< Uncomment this line for iverilog simulation to work
end
function void threadProc_func;
    counter_next = counter;
    counter_next = counter + 1;
endfunction

// Syncrhonous register update
always_ff @(posedge clk or negedge rstn) 
begin : threadProc_ff
    if ( ~rstn ) begin
        counter <= 0;
    end
    else begin
        counter <= counter_next;
    end
end

//------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Method process: methodProc (dut.h:35:5) 

always_comb 
begin : methodProc     // dut.h:35:5
 even = |(counter % 2);
end

endmodule
```
**Design Testbench: `tb_counter.sv`**
```systemverilog
module tb_counter();

logic clk;
logic rstn;
logic [3:0] counter;
logic even;

Dut DUT0(clk, rstn, counter, even);

always
  #10  clk= ~clk;


initial
begin
    rstn = 1;
    clk = 0;
    #20 rstn = 0;

    #30 rstn = 1;

    #500 $finish;
end

initial begin
        if ($test$plusargs("trace") != 0) begin
                $display("[%0t] Tracing to vlt_dump.vcd...\n", $time);
                $dumpfile("logs/vlt_dump.vcd");
                $dumpvars;
        end
        $display("[%0t] Model Running...\n", $time);
end

endmodule
```
Getting the following error while trying out build and run the simulation:

**Iverilog Build command:**
```bash
iverilog -g2012 counter.sv tb_counter.sv -o counter.aout
```
**Output:**
```
counter.sv:27: warning: always_comb process has no sensitivities.
ivl: ../net_scope.cc:500: const NetTaskDef* NetScope::task_def() const: Assertion `type_ == TASK' failed.
```

If one comments the line `28` in `counter.sv` and un-comment the lines `29-30` iverilog is able to extract sensitivity.

Here are the details below for the `iverilog` build from source:

